  "author": "Gunvor Hofmo",
  "title": "Bird",
  "publicationDate": "1990",
  "collectionTitle": "Collection of poems",
  "synopsis": "Gunvor Hofmo's poetry collection Fuglen (The Bird) was published in 1990, towards the end of her prolific career. Known for her free verse style and themes of existential despair and isolation, Hofmo is considered one of Norway's most influential modernist poets. Fuglen explores the human condition through the metaphor of a bird, a symbol of freedom and transcendence",
  "tags": "Tags",
  "poems": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "title": "I don't see the stars",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "I don't see the stars,",
        "but sense the distance,",
        "I no longer walk the roads,",
        "I walk through the centuries,",
        "where cathedrals rise",
        "with a vision of God,",
        "crystallized out of darkness, a",
        "birth paused for",
        "a few millennia",
        "until all spirit shatters"
      ],
      "tags": ["time", "infinity", "spirituality"]
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "title": "It is",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "It is as if the trees",
        "breathe for you,",
        "that you are in the breath",
        "that lives in nocturnal forests, in the meadows",
        "outside the suburbs,",
        "Yes, this breath of the deep",
        "that breathes through millennia",
        "through hidden years",
        "while you fall like a leaf",
        "from the earthly autumn",
        "to the eternal transformation of thought"
      ],
      "tags": ["nature", "breath", "transformation"]
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "title": "The Bird",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "You think it has a nest",
        "with you, the bird,",
        "In your blood shadows",
        "everything The Night over it",
        " ",
        "but suddenly it stands",
        "on the cliff facing the sea,",
        "flooded with sun",
        "and the raw cold of freedom"
      ],
      "tags": ["freedom", "solitude", "nature"]
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "title": "Like a vision...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "Like a vision of",
        "H.C. Andersen's The Mother,",
        "two birches stand in the autumn rain,",
        "One has been touched by God",
        "too soon,",
        "Naked it has forsaken",
        "its possibilities,",
        "But the other lives,",
        "clutches its leaves",
        "close to itself,",
        "as if they were children.",
        "",
        "Wrapping itself in the horizons,",
        "a god who hands out",
        "tickets",
        "to the living land of hope."
      ],
      "tags": ["vision", "autumn", "hope"]
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "title": "It is not...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "It is not the dead",
        "but their silence in me,",
        "it is not human words",
        "but the longing in them,",
        "",
        "that follows me everywhere,",
        "The wind runs ahead of me",
        "and causes the trees to stop,",
        "and speaks to me about the light,",
        "that keeps getting stronger,",
        "",
        "that the night like a horse",
        "stands beyond the horizons,",
        "and chews oats of life's",
        "secrets."
      ],
      "tags": ["silence", "light", "mystery"]
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "title": "Grundtvig",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "The sea carries him.",
        "Currents drive him",
        "outwards and onwards while",
        "the echo of underwater life",
        "hovers in his gaze,",
        "making his tongue speak",
        "words of calm,",
        "words of storm,",
        "",
        "And early in life,",
        "when music reached him,",
        "but it was he who",
        "played on instruments",
        "of Norse myths and the gospel of the bible,",
        "",
        "He builds a house of joy",
        "where the North crafts the furniture",
        "and God is the guest!"
      ],
      "tags": ["sea", "life", "myths"]
    },
    {
      "id": "7",
      "title": "The Story",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "The child throws",
        "the blanket",
        "off itself,",
        "does not want to sleep but falls asleep nonetheless,",
        "",
        "And the child sleeps through centuries,",
        "until a light awakens,",
        "until a sun calls, come",
        "out of your house, human,",
        "for now Ragnarok is over!",
        "The gods in their hall",
        "await the new human."
      ],
      "tags": ["sleep", "awakening", "new era"]
    },
    {
      "id": "8",
      "title": "What are we waiting for...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "What are we really waiting for?",
        "Night follows night,",
        "and the day resounds with echoes",
        "from them,",
        "Paths and streets recognize",
        "something all the time,",
        "a dream awakens to life",
        "in November's pale grass,",
        "And in the woods the squirrel",
        "jumps from tree to tree:",
        "casting shadows over the light",
        "with the Night's secrets,",
        "Fox and marten bite into",
        "November's cold,",
        "so the day transforms into",
        "the wild of darkness"
      ],
      "tags": ["night", "dream", "cold"]
    },
    {
      "id": "9",
      "title": "All has receded...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "All has receded from the room",
        "and fills it again,",
        "in a double knowing",
        "of the secrets of everything,",
        "With a new tongue,",
        "the walls speak,",
        "with a new voice,",
        "silence creates,",
        "the language of the moon,",
        "It shines so",
        "infinitely lonely through",
        "the window,",
        "",
        "And through everything the vision",
        "of generations,",
        "that crumble in your silence,",
        "the one seeking back",
        "through the shadows."
      ],
      "tags": ["emptiness", "secrets", "vision"]
    },
    {
      "id": "10",
      "title": "And His words...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "And His words do not fill",
        "me,",
        "And His voice has gone",
        "into silence,",
        "whose echo sounds",
        "in the Mountains of Sorrow,",
        "But all that is bare",
        "is the forecourt",
        "to the Garden of Paradise."
      ],
      "tags": ["silence", "paradise", "sorrow"]
    },
    {
      "id": "11",
      "title": "A Job's Despair...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "A Job's despair",
        "fills the World,",
        "once hidden",
        "but now evident,",
        "It magnifies",
        "its images",
        "of the refugee's",
        "bitter grief",
        "in bare hotel rooms,",
        "of the dead and dying",
        "in shattered streets,",
        "of children, gaunt",
        "as fence posts,",
        "around the realm of hunger,",
        "where no cows graze",
        "and the grass is nibbled",
        "and brown.",
        "",
        "But who is the photographer?"
      ],
      "tags": ["despair", "visibility", "suffering"]
    },
    {
      "id": "12",
      "title": "SÃ¸rland",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "Still, I feel the sun",
        "like a burning glass",
        "against the cliff,",
        "My skin breathes",
        "of hot stone,",
        "and my body sways",
        "in deep sea without the coolness of water,",
        "",
        "and I see my cat",
        "creeping on its belly",
        "through the heather",
        "after an imaginary",
        "prey"
      ],
      "tags": ["sun", "heat", "illusion"]
    },
    {
      "id": "13",
      "title": "December",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "In the house of winter are",
        "many rooms,",
        "and the room for December",
        "is inhabited by God and Devil,",
        "by Birth and Death,",
        "And Death breathes winter's",
        "chilling winds",
        "around the room,",
        "so the light flickers in the stable",
        "but does not extinguish,",
        "",
        "It does not extinguish, but lives",
        "in the midst of the bitterest darkness"
      ],
      "tags": ["god", "devil", "survival"]
    },
    {
      "id": "14",
      "title": "Nightwatch Song",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "And in the night an echo",
        "of the nightwatch's song",
        "that calls the passing of hours",
        "with a loud voice,",
        "And from the centuries",
        "a lantern light streams",
        "over the sleepless",
        "people,",
        "who feel rain and wind",
        "strike against the pane.",
        "",
        "Who feel that also",
        "the heart is a lantern",
        "lit by calm and trust,",
        "For someone has taken the night",
        "into their hand,",
        "and walks the unknown paths",
        "to the house of light and spirit!"
      ],
      "tags": ["night", "light", "trust"]
    },
    {
      "id": "15",
      "title": "And the patterns",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "And the patterns in everything",
        "eventually stick",
        "in our throats!",
        "Who draws them",
        "and who distributes the copies?",
        "",
        "But the child cannot read:",
        "It only sees strange signs.",
        "",
        "As a child, we should",
        "watch trustingly",
        "the people",
        "who examine the pattern",
        "and not know",
        "what the adults see"
      ],
      "tags": ["patterns", "confusion", "innocence"]
    },
    {
      "id": "16",
      "title": "There are rooms",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "There are rooms",
        "where everything exists,",
        "and the poor know it,",
        "A longing is within them:",
        "that the bare shall transform",
        "into the universe's blooming garden,",
        "that God from the great birth",
        "shall breathe words over",
        "the World beyond all languages!"
      ],
      "tags": ["space", "poverty", "transformation"]
    },
    {
      "id": "17",
      "title": "And yet",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "And yet you hold it fast,",
        "what once God saw through you:",
        "the loops under starlight,",
        "the streets with the silence of loneliness",
        "out of the windows of the low houses,",
        "",
        "and the dusty country roads,",
        "forever past the grocer and post office",
        "in summer vacation,",
        "",
        "Where the sun smelled of dust,",
        "and the body like an otter",
        "cleft the water,",
        "a state of Nirvana,",
        "the struggle ceased."
      ],
      "tags": ["memories", "solitude", "nirvana"]
    },
    {
      "id": "18",
      "title": "Who cries out",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "Who cries out, yes, which voice",
        "resonates from the pine's crown,",
        "murmurs in the stone near the copse?",
        "Winter's dampness makes the sound naked,",
        "as in cities with church towers,",
        "in the silence before the bells",
        "begin to chime,",
        "",
        "Everything that dissolves in the World's",
        "deep consciousness..."
      ],
      "tags": ["voice", "nature", "consciousness"]
    },
    {
      "id": "19",
      "title": "Who",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "Who shall these lawns",
        "and forests",
        "embrace after you?",
        "Will the great wave of light",
        "also pass over them,",
        "",
        "the one that makes the sea transparent",
        "so you recognize",
        "the sunken boats:",
        "your many lives!",
        "Left to a naked",
        "awareness of secret worlds,",
        "they send cries",
        "through crabs",
        "and fish,",
        "in solidarity with your",
        "first birth."
      ],
      "tags": ["legacy", "transparency", "secret worlds"]
    },
    {
      "id": "20",
      "title": "It has rained...",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "It has rained,",
        "and it chains",
        "our lives together,",
        "Everything is part of the rain:",
        "The room, the streets, and the plains",
        "burst as from a chrysalis",
        "into a new, terrible",
        "light."
      ],
      "tags": ["connection", "renewal", "revelation"]
    },
    {
      "id": "21",
      "title": "Poet",
      "date": "Unknown",
      "text": [
        "You search for the words",
        "as if they were birds",
        "flown away from you,",
        "and force them back",
        "from the horizons,",
        "from new landscapes,",
        "And they return home,",
        "carrying the rustle of great forests,",
        "and the thunder of the sea..."
      ],
      "tags": ["search", "return", "nature's roar"]
    }
  ]
}
